24 de ceteris . . . multa . . . hunc librum . . . de senectute: note 3 the elaborate chiasmus.—ceteris: other topics of philosophy (easily inferred from the preceding sentence), not ‘other matters in general,' in which case rebus would be regularly employed. Cicero uses a similar method of transition in Tusc. 4, 5: sed de ceteras studiis alio loco et dice- mus et saepe diximus. Here studiis is necessary to make the thought clear.
